3.2.1 Named arguments
	- when calling a function written in Kotlin, you can specify the names of some of the arguments that you're passing to the function.
		ex)
			===============================================
			joinToString(
				postFix = ".",
				separator = " ",
				collection = collection,
				prefix = " "
			)
			===============================================

	- IntelliJ IDEA and Android Studio can keep explicitly written argument names up to date if you rename the parameter of the function being called.
	